FBIS4-28472 "dreas112__a94007" FBIS-EAS-94-112-A Daily Report 9 Jun 1994 ANNEX Japan More Reports on Issues Related to DPRK More Reports on Issues Related to DPRK Hata on Effectiveness of UN Sanctions OW0906140394 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 9 Jun 94 Morning Edition p 2 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY OW0906140394 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN Japanese BFN [Text] At a House of Representatives' Budget Committee meeting on 8 June, Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata commented on the DPRK's suspected development of nuclear weapons. He said: "The situation will become serious if nuclear arms development should progress. In some cases, sanctions will be necessary to deal with such a situation. In a conflict of power, I think (imposing sanctions) is effective under certain circumstances." In this way, the prime minister stressed the effectiveness of sanctions by the UN Security Council.
